by student HaoYuan Jiang WatID 20371798

*** This program is written in Java ***

To compile this program:
Make sure you are in the folder that contains the 2 .java files and Makefile.
Type "make" will compile both the server and the client.

To run the server:
Type "java server"
A line will be printed to stdout showing the port number used for negotiation.

To run the client:
Type "java client <host name> <port number for negotiation> <message>"
These 3 parameters are separated by space not including the <> sign.
Server response message will be printed out.

This program is tested in maclab MC3004 both on localhost
and with one IMac running the client whilte another running the server.
